Revision history for lb, a very small and efficient Libevent-based benchmark tool for HTTP servers.


Changes in version 0.2.6 - 2016-07-11 - Rocco Carbone <rocco@tecsiel.it>
  (+) moved to github


Changes in version 0.2.5 - 2015-02-14 - Rocco Carbone <rocco@tecsiel.it>
  (+) compile out of the libevent 2.0.22-stable source tree


Changes in version 0.2.4 - 2013-11-12 - Rocco Carbone <rocco@tecsiel.it>
  (+) compile out of the libevent 2.0.21-stable source tree


Changes in version 0.2.3 - 2012-02-07 - Rocco Carbone <rocco@tecsiel.it>
  (+) compile out of the libevent 2.0.16-stable source tree


Changes in version 0.2.2 - 2009-07-22 - Rocco Carbone <rocco@tecsiel.it>
  (+) Implementation of global duration time per session (see -t option)
  (+) HTTP Keep-Alive (see -k option)
  (+) HTTP HEAD (see -i option)
  (+) Arbitrary HTTP headers (see -H option)
  (+) Arbitrary HTTP cookies (see -C option)
  (+) Basic HTTP authentication
  (+) HTTP Proxy server support (see -X option)
  (+) Basic HTTP proxy authentication (see -P option)


Changes in version 0.2.1 - 2009-07-17 - Rocco Carbone <rocco@tecsiel.it>
  (+) Improvements to the GNU Build System in order to compile out of
      the libevent svn tree and check for libevent-2.x availability


Changes in version 0.2.0 - 2009-07-16 - Rocco Carbone <rocco@tecsiel.it>
  (+) Use the GNU Build System
  (+) Major performance improvements
      - An array of 'concurrency' items is maintained in memory per server
	in order to avoid the malloc/free nightmares for all the requests.
	The libevent 'evcon' is allocated just once while one 'evreq'
	is allocated per request.
	This simple change allowed to drammatically increase the performances


Changes in version 0.1.0 - 2009-07-08 - Rocco Carbone <rocco@tecsiel.it>
  (+) First public release announced to Libevent mailing list and freshmeat.net


Changes in version 0.0.1 - 2009-07-04 - Rocco Carbone <rocco@tecsiel.it>
  (+) Start development
